	<h3>Our Cosmetic Dental Services</h3>
	<p>
		We combine artistry with advanced dental science to deliver beautiful results.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Professional Teeth Whitening:</strong> Achieve a smile several shades brighter in just one visit. Our clinical-grade whitening treatments are safer and far more effective than over-the-counter strips.</li>
		<li><strong>Porcelain Veneers:</strong> Thin, custom-crafted porcelain shells that cover the front surface of your teeth to instantly correct chips, gaps, or severe discoloration.</li>
		<li><strong>Dental Bonding:</strong> A quick and cost-effective way to repair minor chips or close small gaps using tooth-colored composite resin.</li>
		<li><strong>Invisalign Clear Aligners:</strong> Subtly straighten your teeth without metal brackets. <a href="/invisalign-braces">Learn more about Invisalign</a>.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>The Smile Makeover Process</h3>
	<p>
		Every great smile begins with a plan. During your cosmetic consultation, we will discuss your goals, take digital photographs, and evaluate your oral health. We can often provide digital mock-ups so you can preview your new smile before any treatment begins!
	</p>

	<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
	<details>
		<summary>Is cosmetic dentistry covered by insurance or CDCP?</summary>
		<p>No, treatments performed purely for aesthetic reasons (like teeth whitening or veneers) are not covered by the <a href="/cdcp-dentist">Canadian Dental Care Plan (CDCP)</a> or most private insurance plans. However, treatments that also restore function (like a crown for a broken tooth) may have partial coverage.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>Does teeth whitening damage enamel?</summary>
		<p>When performed by a dental professional, teeth whitening is completely safe and does not damage your enamel. You may experience temporary tooth sensitivity, but this subsides quickly.</p>
	</details>

